BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260604T223000Z
DTEND:20260605T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260604T000000Z
SUMMARY:Hamilton: The Musical and the Duel
DESCRIPTION:A Rev250 Program\n\nfeaturing Rick Feingold\n\nIt is an 
 entertaining and informative look at Hamilton—the play and the 
 revolutionary who inspired it.\n\nHamilton\, a ground-breaking musical 
 featuring Black and Latino actors playing the founding fathers\, won 11 
 Tony awards. Alexander Hamilton\, an immigrant who became the first 
 Secretary of the Treasury and founded the U.S. financial system\, died at 
 the hands of Vice President Aaron Burr upon the dueling grounds in 
 Weehawken\, NJ.\n\nLearn about the history behind the characters in this 
 fun presentation that includes the Hamilton mix-tape performance at the 
 White House and music from the Broadway production.\n\nAbout the 
 presenter\n\nRick Feingold teaches American history at Bergen Community 
 College. He holds a BA in history from Rutgers University and an MBA from 
 Penn State University.
LOCATION:West Orange - Community Room 1
ORGANIZER;CN="West Orange Library":MAILTO:events@westorange.bccls.org
CATEGORIES:Lecture
UID:LibCal-10341-16644214
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16644214
END:VEVENT
