SUMMARY:"Let's Celebrate America with Our Hit Songs 30's to 50's" with Ellen LaFurn
DESCRIPTION:With Ellen Lafurn\n\nEnjoy the nostalgic musical event that is 
 being hosted by jazz soprano Ellen LaFurn\, which is titled "Let's 
 Celebrate America with Our Hit Songs 30's to 50's." Take advantage of this 
 fantastic opportunity to witness swinging American jazz in its classic 
 form.\n\n \n\nArtist information\n\nI began singing professionally when I 
 was 17 years old with Chang Lee and the Zaniacs\, a "show group." Before 
 this\, I sang at teen parties and clubs\, and once I was with Little 
 Anthony & the Imperials. I joined Jerry Mitchell and the Impacts and worked 
 with and learned from Roland Hanna\, Gus Johnson\, Danny Gibson\, and my 
 friend Miss Rhapsody\, among others. Then there was the Joe Zarr trio\, 
 which had the late Al Ross on organ and Warren Battiste on guitar. During 
 this time\, I also worked with The Traces and the Gary Kay Trio.\n\n
LOCATION:West Orange - Community Room 1
ORGANIZER;CN="West Orange Library":MAILTO:events@westorange.bccls.org
CATEGORIES:Performance
