BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260628T173000Z
DTEND:20260628T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260628T000000Z
SUMMARY:Life Tapestries: A Felt Quilting Workshop
DESCRIPTION:\n\nwith Donelle Wedderburn\n\nAs part of this summer's Unearth 
 a Story theme\, we invite you to explore and share your own family story 
 through this craft workshop that blends family cartography and pictorial 
 mapmaking. Using felt application\, participants will create a quilt square 
 that maps the people\, neighborhoods\, and migration pathways that have 
 shaped their lives. \n\nPictorial mapmaking occupies a space between art 
 and science\, relying on codes\, symbols\, and visual storytelling. The 
 connection between cartography and quilting is especially potent\, as both 
 practices share this symbolic language. To ground their work\, participants 
 will learn about and reference the work of artists like Louise E. Jefferson 
 and Valerie Goodwin. \n\nNo sewing skills required. All supplies will be 
 provided. Participants are also invited to bring meaningful fabric scraps 
 or materials they would like to incorporate into their 
 project.\n\nRegistration is required. This workshop is designed for adults. 
 Teens and tweens ages 10  are welcome if participating alongside an adult. 
 Each participant--adult and youth--must be registered 
 individually.\n\nAbout the Artist\n\nDonelle Wedderburn is a 
 Jamaican-American writer and teaching artist who explores how memory and 
 land shape one another\, and how stories can be carried across landscapes\, 
 built environments\, and collective memory. Inspired by Black women writers 
 such as Toni Morrison and June Jordan\, who moved fluidly between narrative 
 and spatial imagination\, she sees storytelling as a practice that can 
 shape not only language\, but also the spaces we inhabit.\n\n \n\n
LOCATION:West Orange - Community Room 1\, West Orange Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="West Orange Library":MAILTO:events@westorange.bccls.org
CATEGORIES:Craft, Special Event
UID:LibCal-10341-16413222
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16413222
END:VEVENT
