BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260822T180000Z
DTEND:20260822T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260822T000000Z
SUMMARY:Unearthing Our Past: Revolutionary Stories
DESCRIPTION:Unearthing Our Past: Revolutionary Stories\n\nPresented by West 
 Orange Township Historian Joseph Fagan\n\nWest Orange Public Library – 
 August 16\, 2026 – 2pm\n\n \n\nJoin West Orange Township Historian Joseph 
 Fagan as he unearths the many stories forgotten by time at the Old Burying 
 Ground in nearby Orange. Here weathered gravestones and forgotten burial 
 plots reveal the many stories of West Orange’s first settlers. Join 
 Joseph Fagan as he steps through an undisturbed portal in time where 
 Revolutionary War patriots\, local families\, and ordinary citizens still 
 bear silent witness to history. Discover the stories of the people whose 
 lives\, sacrifices\, and experiences helped shape both our local community 
 and the nation.\n\n \n\nPresented as part of the commemoration of 
 America’s 250th anniversary\, this program is the second in a series by 
 Joseph Fagan supporting Rev250 NJ. It is a statewide initiative that 
 explores the unique Revolutionary War history of communities across New 
 Jersey. Join Fagan for an engaging journey into the people\, events\, and 
 stories that helped define our nation and continue to shape our local 
 heritage today.\n\n \n\n\n \n
LOCATION:West Orange - Community Room 1
ORGANIZER;CN="West Orange Library":MAILTO:events@westorange.bccls.org
CATEGORIES:
UID:LibCal-10341-16981871
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16981871
END:VEVENT
